<hr />
<p>The Housing &amp; Student Living Office works with students to help  them make the most of their living situations while attending school  here. To do so, we provide both on-campus housing and off-campus support  and regulation.</p>
<p><a href="x9252.xml">On-Campus Housing</a> is available for both single students and student-families. It provides an inexpensive, close-to-campus option for matriculating students.</p>
<p><a href="x9514.xml">Single Student Approved Housing</a> provides a unique opporunity for our  office to help ensure students have housing that is physically and  spiritually conducive to fulfilling the mission of BYU-Idaho. We provide education, mediation and arbitration services to help resolve issues in Approved Housing.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.byui.edu/studentliving">Student Living</a> provides teaching and support opporunities to help roommates, friends and families strengthen communication and encourage integrity.</p>
<p>If you have any questions or concerns about your housing or living situation, we invite you to <a href="x15577.xml">contact us</a> and we'd be more than happy to do what we can to help you.</p>
